WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.140
So in business, people see kind of new shiny tools and technologies, and they immediately

00:00:05.140 --> 00:00:09.240
pivot to this is exactly what we need, we need AI here yesterday.

00:00:09.240 --> 00:00:15.040
And I think in some cases, you know, companies may not have data in a position where it is,

00:00:15.040 --> 00:00:21.520
you know, ideal to kind of, you know, send off to a GPT model, for example, there might

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:24.040
be other kind of pre processing steps that may need to happen.

00:00:24.040 --> 00:00:27.920
But I think in general, it's learning more about kind of the the limitations and also

00:00:27.920 --> 00:00:31.000
where you know, like a generative AI model excels.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:36.040
So it's, you know, mostly around generating content, and can help you facilitate having

00:00:36.040 --> 00:00:40.759
a conversation with a body of knowledge is another way that I tend to think about generative

00:00:40.759 --> 00:00:41.759
AI models.

00:00:41.759 --> 00:00:45.919
And, you know, seeing what kind of problem spaces these models, you know, excel in, and

00:00:45.919 --> 00:00:50.680
I think it's really just around practicing with them, and getting an understanding of

00:00:50.680 --> 00:00:54.400
what they can do, and what they can't do to help inform, you know, okay, now that I have

00:00:54.400 --> 00:00:57.560
an understanding, what what business challenge can I maybe apply this to?

